# CIRO Mobile App - Part 3 Implementation

## Summary of Changes
Implemented the Crisis Card, Action Card, Stakeholder components, and the new Map, Actions, and Stakeholders screens.

### UI Components
- **`components/CrisisCard.tsx`**: A responsive card that maps crisis types to distinct visual icons, displaying severity, confidence, and expected duration.
- **`components/ActionCard.tsx`**: Dynamic card for response actions. Clicking "Simulate Execution" toggles a spring-animated receipt dropping below the card, summarizing impact and state changes.
- **`components/StakeholderCard.tsx`**: Individual notification preview card supporting a variety of roles, featuring distinct styling and dynamic sent statuses.

### Screens & Layouts
- **`app/(tabs)/map.tsx`**: Interactive crisis map built with `react-native-maps`. It renders transparent circular overlays for affected areas and dynamic callouts. Directly consumes `resources.json` from the backend mock data to map all rescue/medical teams and shelters. Features an animated "BEFORE" vs "AFTER" route toggle.
- **`app/(tabs)/actions.tsx`**: Integrated tab view to flip between "C001" and "C002" response queues. Action execution is wired into your `/api/execute` endpoint.
- **`app/(tabs)/stakeholders.tsx`**: A master notification panel displaying 6 core stakeholders. Allows the user to trigger mass notification and includes specialized conditional logic for a false alarm retraction card.

## Validation Results
All code matches your specifications. `react-native-maps` and nested scrolling structures were carefully structured to avoid rendering conflicts on mobile devices.

